    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "i get that they're both valid frameworks, but in a real debate setting, isn't it kind of a stretch to call the border security argument \"morally defensible\" if it leads to families being separated or people being turned away from danger? like, wouldn't most modern ethics say that human life is objectively more important than a line on a map?",
