    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "but if the humanitarian side is \"significantly stronger,\" isn't it basically saying that the whole concept of national sovereignty is just an outdated or even immoral idea? if the moral claim is that much heavier, why do we even treat border security as a legitimate debate point instead of just seeing it as an obstacle to doing the right thing?",
